<TITLE> Muhith eyes plan for sick industries </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 03 (bdnews24.com)  Finance Minister AMA Muhith said the government will set a policy for the country's 700 or so sick industries. But he said the industries that have remained ineffective over a period of 15 years have no right get support. "The Sick Industries Association is disgraceful," Muhith said after his meeting with the leaders of the organisation on Thursday. Of the sick industries, 270 units are in garment sector, 108 specialised textile mills and 80 tanneries. Chowdhury Mohammad Iqbal, the chief of the association, discussed with the finance minister ways to revive the sick industries. Iqbal sought withdrawal of cases against 200 sick units. He later told reporters: "The industries become sick mainly because of (wrong) policies of commercial banks and the government
